The cops have recovered a state vehicle belonging to Gauteng
MEC for Sports, Arts, Culture and Recreation, Faith Mazibuko. The car was hijacked on Saturday and recovered on Monday
morning. Mazibuko's security detail was waiting by her car in the
Joburg CBD to escort her to a meeting when armed men took the vehicle. The intelligence driven operation led to the arrest of
four suspects and the recovery of the Mercedes Benz ML 500. "Within 48 hours the hard work of the team paid off
when they arrested four suspects and recovered the hijacked vehicle," Captain
Mavela Masondo. The suspects were arrested in Eldorado Park in the early
hours of Monday. They were found in
possession of the hijacked vehicle, firearm believed to be the one taken from
Mazibuko's protection team and another unlicensed firearm. The suspects will be charged with hijacking, kidnapping
as well as possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition. They will appear at
Johannesburg Magistrateâ€™s Court in due course.